---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const supportEmail = "linguico.app@gmail.com";
const effectiveDate = "May 20, 2026";
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Vista Weather"
  description="Vista Weather privacy policy for iOS: data is never sold, and location is only used to fetch the forecast."
>
  <div class="page privacy-page">
    <div class="page-frame" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <header class="masthead">
      <a class="wordmark wordmark-link" href={baseUrl} aria-label="Vista Weather home">
        <span class="wordmark-name">Vista&nbsp;Weather</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="policy-nav" aria-label="Privacy navigation">
        <a class="kicker" href={baseUrl}>Home</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <div class="rule" style="margin-top:14px"></div>

    <main class="policy">
      <section class="policy-hero" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
        <p class="kicker">Privacy Policy</p>
        <h1 id="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="policy-lede">
          Vista Weather is designed to collect as little data as possible. Your data is never sold to
          advertisers or third parties. Your location is only used to fetch the forecast.
        </p>

        <div class="policy-summary" aria-label="Privacy summary">
          <div>
            <span>Never sold</span>
            <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span>Forecast only</span>
            <p>Location is used only to show weather for your area.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span>No tracking</span>
            <p>We do not track you across other companies' apps or websites.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="policy-updated">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-body" aria-label="Privacy policy details">
        <h2>Scope</h2>
        <p>
          This policy explains how Vista Weather handles information in the Vista Weather mobile app
          and on the Vista Weather website.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect only the information needed to provide the app and respond to requests you make.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Location.</strong> If you allow location access, Vista Weather uses your device's
            location to request the forecast for your area. We do not keep a history of your location.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Searches and saved places.</strong> If you search for or save a place in the app,
            that place may be used to show its forecast. Saved places are stored on your device unless
            the app clearly tells you otherwise.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Email address.</strong> If you join the waitlist or contact support, we collect the
            email address and message you provide so we can send the requested update or respond to you.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Basic website delivery data.</strong> Our website host may process standard server
            log data, such as IP address, browser type, and request time, to deliver and protect the
            website. We do not use this data for advertising or tracking.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To fetch and display weather forecasts.</li>
          <li>To remember places you choose to save on your device.</li>
          <li>To send launch or product updates you requested.</li>
          <li>To respond to support, privacy, or deletion requests.</li>
          <li>To maintain, secure, and improve the app and website.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Location</h2>
        <p>
          Location access is optional and controlled by iOS. If you grant permission, Vista Weather may
          send your current location or an approximate location to a weather service provider only as
          needed to return the forecast. Your location is not used for advertising, sold to anyone, or
          used to build a profile about you.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We may use service providers, such as weather data providers, website hosting providers, and
          email delivery providers, to operate Vista Weather. These providers may process data only to
          provide their services to us, and they must protect user data at least as carefully as this
          policy requires.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not use third-party advertising SDKs, data brokers, or tracking services.
        </p>

        <h2>Retention and Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Location used to fetch a forecast is not retained by Vista Weather after the forecast request
          is served. Saved places and cached app data are stored on your device and can be removed by
          deleting them in the app, where available, or by deleting the app.
        </p>
        <p>
          Waitlist and support emails are kept only as long as needed to send requested updates, provide
          support, meet legal obligations, or maintain basic business records. You can request deletion
          of your email or support messages at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Choices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            You can grant, deny, or revoke location permission in iOS Settings under
            Privacy &amp; Security, then Location Services, then Vista Weather.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Vista Weather is not directed to children under 13, and we do not collect personal
          information from children under 13.
        </p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards to protect personal
          data. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, but we design Vista Weather to
          minimize the data we handle.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy as Vista Weather changes. If we make material changes, we will update
          the effective date and provide additional notice when appropriate.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions or deletion requests, email
          <a href={`mailto:${supportEmail}`}>{supportEmail}</a>.
        </p>

      </section>
    </main>

    <div class="rule" style="margin:32px 0 16px"></div>

    <footer class="foot">
      <div class="kicker">Vista&nbsp;Weather&nbsp;&copy;&nbsp;2026</div>
      <div class="kicker" style="text-align:center">Coming&nbsp;soon &middot; iOS &middot; Android</div>
      <div class="kicker" style="text-align:right">
        <a href={`mailto:${supportEmail}`}>Support</a> &middot; <a href={`${baseUrl.replace(/\/$/, "")}/privacy/`}>Privacy</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>
